profile_positions.description:
▪ Represent the youth wing of the largest Dutch trade union internationally;
▪ Inform the membership on international affairs and involve youth members in international 
forums and initiatives.

▪ Covering trade unions in the EST Youth Employment working group;
▪ Developed and disseminated research products on strategies to increase labor’s influence on 
EU employment policy-making.

▪ Independent research project on Euro-American labor cooperation and sustainability in 
global labor governance (specifically Global Framework Agreements);
▪ Conducted strategic research for workers’ centers in the New York area.

▪ Oversaw the publication of 4 editions of this political youth magazine per year throughout my tenure;
▪ Coordinated an editorial team of 15+ contributors; 
▪ For LAVA's digital database, go to: http://issuu.com/lava.digital/docs

▪ Conducted field research on unauthorized Palestinian workers’ unionization; 
▪ Conducted international comparative research supporting an appeal to the Israeli Supreme 
Court over the country’s labor migration regime.

▪ Assisted lecturer and former BBC war correspondent A. van Lynden with research support 
on war and regime change in the Middle East;
▪ Provided feedback on first year students’ homework and essays.
